<br>
The end game is based on one spell. Complete heal.  Without it noone will take out aow, tomax, sleeper, whatever.<br>
<br>
Saying that some direct heal can do xxx amount of healing has no meaning in the end game. The only heal spell that matters in cheal and how many clerics you have to keep your tanks alive.  Now on to what a druid (shammy too) is casting on these raids is chloroblast. Druids/shammy use this spell to keep the cheal casting clerics alive. As well as wizzies and the debuffers (shammy and chanters).<br>
<br>
A better direct heal for druids and shammy will not infringe on clerics. How so?<br>
<br>
On end game raids, clerics are there to cast cheals and devine light if someone is too low on hps for a cheal to land. And res folks after and during the battle and send the newly ressed tanks back into the fight. A better direct heal for druids and shammy means they to can heal tanks taking damage from aes or other stray hits.<br>
<br>
On normal exp groups. Clerics when you can find one can handle all the heals. Druids and shammy heal the cleric and chanter when cleric is healing tanks. If no cleric available? The druids are healing in the group cause shammy need to use their mana to slow. Shammy slowing is more important than shammy healing in a exp groups. A better direct heal for shammy and druids lets them fill the role of healer better when there is no cleric.  Personally, I would (I am sure it applies to everyone else) rather have a cleric as primary healer in my groups. So where are all the clerics that exp groups cann't get any? They all been invited to raid tomax, vp, ntov, or ssra temple is where all the clerics disappeared too. And all the druids and shammy are left with looking for a group somewhere. And on these high level raids anyone would rather have another cleric instead of another druid (assuming you have one druid there to buff folks). I know I would, and so would you if you are truthful with yourself. Along with rogues, warriors, or monks before I would take a second druid. The only reason for having more than 1 druid is because the raid is lacking enough clerics to heal groups verses the MT and being in the cheal rotation.<br>
<br>
As to the ever decreasing druid population? I think druids still make up the most populated class in the game. It's just alot of us play alts instead. Or are roleplay to avoid the tell hell asking to be pled by some stranger. Oh please pl me 3 levels, I'll give yah 30pp for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     My responce has always been, I turn down offers of 1k an hour. Since I would rather be playing than being bored pling someone else.<br>
<br>
Maybe what is wanted instead of a better heal is increase the percent chance that healing adept works. Being able to pop off a 1780 hp heal makes a big difference to a tank surviving.  But just how useful would it be? I know I never wait for the tank to get below 70% before casting nature's touch on 'em. And casting chloroblast on casters as soon as they get summoned or get hit and are at 80%.  The double heal only helps when multiple critters in camp and folks are being pounded into the ground.<br>
<br>
As for torpal. I really don't know how rare the spell is. But if it anything like 60 level kunark druids spells then I can understand shammy fustration over the spell.<br>
<br>
As for its usefullness? It saves my no AC behind all the time while being pounded into the ground by multiple critters for thinking of casting a chloroblast on the chanter.  This comes in very nicely in the new CT. Also our shammy uses it to pull when we know there is HT critters that are next to be pulled. It lets her stand there and get attacked by critters without getting below 50% health. Of course I tossed in a chloroblast on top of torpal. And as soon as stuff is mezzed and the tanks are beating one up. Her hps are maxed in no time. It is a great spell to cast on non melees that are being pounded into the ground including your cleric and your's truly that no AC druid (that's me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <p><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#FF00FF"><b><I>Tsulyra Shadowhawk</I></b></font><br><b>
